      "content": "hERG blockers commonly have:\n- **A protonated basic N** to form electrostatic interactions in the channel vestibule (often with residues such as **Tyr/Phe** via cation\u2013\u03c0 and with polar residues via ion pairing).\n- **Two lipophilic/aromatic moieties** to engage the hydrophobic cavity and \u03c0-stacking.\n- **Appropriate length** (often ~8\u201312 \u00c5 between key features) and conformational flexibility to adopt the binding pose.",
