      "step_index": 5,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "In this molecule:\n- The **permanently protonated tertiary ammonium** strongly favors binding (electrostatic/cation\u2013\u03c0).\n- The **aryl-rich, bulky region** (fluorophenyl + fused aromatic ether system) provides **large hydrophobic surface area** and \u03c0-systems\u2014good for the canonical hERG aromatic interactions.\n- The **butyl linker** gives enough reach/flexibility for the cation to sit near the channel\u2019s electronegative region while the aromatic bulk occupies the hydrophobic pocket.\n- The **nitrile** can subtly tune electronics and may increase polarity slightly, but it typically **does not eliminate** hERG risk when the core cationic/aromatic pharmacophore is strong.",
